				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="21">Battle for Gfay -Sullon Zek</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Mage of the 8th season</b></a>
				[7/16/2001-2:16:26 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=467986"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[15]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
Hearing cries for help as the sun rose on the Greater Faydark, I swung by Butcher Block mountains. As I slowly closed in to the BB zone line, I saw a dozen or more high elven and wood elven corpses. Upon wondering what masacre had occured here, I heared the shouts for help within BB as the neutral races were pushing any characters of light back in to Gfay where we 'belonged'.
Slowly, yet surely, a force of Goods united outside of the BB zone line. Healing and medding, we slowly prepared to enter BB and meet the Neutral force, head on.</p>
<p>
Unprepared and unaware, over 15 dwarfs and gnomes poured in to the small valley which links Gfay and BB. In a blur of violence, we were retreating to the trees of Kelethin having fallen to so many neutrals.</p>
<p>
Pushing their invasion forward, the force of neutrals hastily made their way to the entrance of Crushbone, slaying any child of light that set foot in their path. Upon hearing their entry in to Crushbone, we amassed a force large in number, and determined in spirit, outside the zone line of Crushbone.</p>
<p>
Weaker in level, and worn out by the masacre at BB entrance, we sought a plan to gain us advantage over the neutral force which had taken Crushbone and sent players of light scrambling for zone lines. Our plan was to form a wall directly infront of the zone line to Crushbone, and take out every neutral as they zoned, one at a time and unprepared, out of Crushbone. And surely that's what they did. One by one, they appeared infront of us, horrified by what they faced, yet bound by the roots of earth. We quickly gained the advantage as over half of their force had fallen to us outside Crushbone. Calling more to arms, we strengthend in numbers and entered Crushbone, hunting down the last neutrals with every shred of vengence we could conjure.</p>
<p>
The sun set slowly that day in Greater Faydark, as we allowed the neutrals safe passage to their corpses, and smiled victoriously as they fell back to their homes within the Butcher Block mountains.
Although we grieved for our fallen friends, we had proven that the Good side hits back, when struck. The battle for Faydwer rages on, as tommorrow is another day.</p>
<p>
