				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="31">Second Anniversary of A`dileab de Paegen on Tunare</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Invectus Stormborn</b></a>
				[7/13/2001-3:15:11 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=466823"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[3]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
Second Anniversary of A`dileab de Paegen on Tunare, Sunday, July 15th - all day</p>
<p>
Our 2nd anniversary as a guild is coming up and we want to do something special for it. For the entire 24 hours of July 15th, we are dropping our normal hunting, questing and raiding activities in order to Save the World.</p>
<p>
What I mean by that, is that for the entire day, we will wander Norrath and look for people in need of help. There are many ways we will be doing this:</p>
<p>
- you may hear us shout that we are giving out free buffs and heals<br>
- or that we are stopping trains and acting as guards<br>
- or you may suddenly find us doing the same quietly and unannounced - depending on the member's style<br>
- we will find the lost and clueless(yes, there still are some) and guide them to where they need to go<br>
- during busier hours we will station people in specific zones to act as 'aid stations' for the people in the zone<br>
- starting around Noon, Central Time, we will group up in Qeynos and begin travelling from zone to zone across Norrath, spending about 15-20 mins in each zone, helping everyone we meet along the way<br>
- when not otherwise occupied we will be giving out free teleports to wherever<br>
- and in general, if anyone needs any help of any kind - we will give it to the best of our ability on a first come-first served basis</p>
<p>
You can read more at our guild website: <a href="http://adileab.50megs.com">http://adileab.50megs.com</a></p>
<p>
Invectus Stormborn<br>
Wizard of the 48th Circle<br>
Leader of A`dileab de Paegen<br>
Tunare Server</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
