				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="40">EverQuest: Elseworlds is back!</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:rl_ryoma@yahoo.com">Ryoma Cinderbane</b></a>
				[7/12/2001-12:04:48 PM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=466247"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[8]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
Hail all.</p>
<p>
Those of you who follow the comic strip "EverCrest" by Tim Fries may remember the "Elseworlds" series that appeared alongside EverCrest for a short time.</p>
<p>
I was the artist of Elseworlds.  I apologize to all those who sent me encouraging letters during my short time with EverCrest...some things in life came up that forced me to stop drawing the series, and indeed stop playing EverQuest, for over a year.</p>
<p>
Well....now I'm back in EQ, and Elseworlds is back also!  I decided to put Elseworlds on its own site this time, so that I may have more freedom with my style.  For those of you who remember the old Elseworlds, some of the characters you know still remain, and I have added several new ones to replace extinct characters.</p>
<p>
Also, I can no longer call it "EverCrest: Elseworlds", obviously, because I am no longer affiliated with EverCrest....so in a burst of creativity I renamed it "EverQuest: Elseworlds".</p>
<p>
The old Elseworlds series can be found at the following address(click on the yellowish dates):</p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.evercrest.com/archives/1999">http://www.evercrest.com/archives/1999</a></p>
<p>
And the new Elseworlds site address is as follows:</p>
<p>
<a href="http://www.the-dudes.net/Elseworlds/Elseworlds.html">http://www.the-dudes.net/Elseworlds/Elseworlds.html</a></p>
<p>
If you get a chance, go check it out.</p>
<p>
-Ryoma</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
