				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="43">The Battle of Blackburrow:  Sullon Zek</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:btrahan@midsouth.rr.com">Mihwa</b></a>
				[7/12/2001-11:52:51 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=466075"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[22]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
<p>
The Battle of Blackburrow<br>
(in character)</p>
<p>
As I entered Blackburrow after dropping off some recent booty, something didn't seem quite right. There were more corpses lying about than from the usual trains of gnolls spilling down to the entrance.</p>
<p>
I shrugged it off and headed back to my favorite hunting spot. I had been successful prying several teeth from the mouths of the dead reptiles and was looking forward to a night of fine profit.</p>
<p>
As I headed towards the door leading to my prey, a strange feeling overcame me ... as if I were shrugging off an attempt to be rooted in place. The next eerie feeling came in the form of a strange barking sound in my head.</p>
<p>
Villains! The so-called 'good' of Everfrost was invading! The poor hapless bodies of several young adventurers were laying strewn about the cavern as I raced deeper inside. "Don't panic!", I said to myself. I needed to find a safe corner. I leaped off a ledge and ducked around a corner, panting frantically. I reached inside my pouch and covered myself with some magic dust and faded into my surroundings.</p>
<p>
I had to scout out the enemy, and what an enemy! Dozens and dozens of those goodie goodies were chasing down my brothers and sisters, hacking mercilessly at their vulnerable bodies, shocking them with lightning and singing them with fire.</p>
<p>
I cried inwardly and strengthened my resolve. I reached back into my pouch and spread some dust around the floor ... praying to the Gods of Nature to take me back to Qeynos. A few moments later I arrived in Qeynos to chaos! Everyone was shouting that the goods had taken BlackBurrow!</p>
<p>
With a mighty call to arms, many of us rushed back to confront the hoard, but we had sadly underestimated their strength! As we tried to re-enter Blackburrow, we were stopped by a mighty wall of warriors and casters. We tried again and again to no avail. They were just to strong!</p>
<p>
But behold! A mighty shout came out that another group of brothers and sisters were on the way! With a cry of defiance, we rushed back thru to face the invaders! Several of us died, many of us were hurt badly, but we were determined to weaken the foes until our reinforcements arrived. Suddenly, through the tunnel they came! And what an army we had. The enemy line started wavering as a mighty battle ensued! And soon they started to fall, and then they started to run.</p>
<p>
Showing similar compassion as the enemy, we chased them down and hacked them to bits! We held them magically in place while our warrior brethren bloodied their swords. We drove them all the way back through their tunnel to Everfrost!</p>
<p>
But ho! We weren't finished. The blood of our brothers and sisters cried for more! We formed into groups and blast our way into their homeland. As we entered the frigid air of Everfrost, we were met by a reinforced hoard of good! But our hearts cried out for our fallen, and we plunged into their ranks!</p>
<p>
Many of them were already weak from our previous battle, and many were poorly equipped, and we tore through them with a vengeance! We decimated their forces and chased them deep into the snowy plains of Everfrost.</p>
<p>
As they came back to retrieve their corpses, we mercilessly slaughtered them. Finally, when our thirst for blood had been satiated, we allowed them to grab their belongings and run back home to lick their wounds. We left them with a final warning never to enter Blackburrow again, or face the same fate!</p>
<p>
Now, all is quiet back on my ledge, and the snake fang business is back on track.</p>
<p>
Mihwa<br>
13th level druid<br>
Reaper for life, Reaper of Death!</p>
</blockquote>
</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
